Sentencas: In this paper, a kinetic model for the catalytic dehydrogenation of perhydro dibenzyltoluene (H18-DBT), a well-established Liquid Organic Hydrogen Carrier (LOHC) compound, is presented.
Titulo: A solid oxide fuel cell operating on liquid organic hydrogen carrier-based hydrogen A kinetic model of the hydrogen release unit and system performance

Sentencas: Kinetic parameters for hydrogen release at a Pt on alumina catalyst in a temperature range between 260 degrees C and 310 degrees C are presented.
Titulo: A solid oxide fuel cell operating on liquid organic hydrogen carrier-based hydrogen A kinetic model of the hydrogen release unit and system performance

Sentencas: A Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) system model was coupled to the hydrogen release from H18-DBT in order to validate the full sequence of LOHC-bound hydrogen-to-electric power.
Titulo: A solid oxide fuel cell operating on liquid organic hydrogen carrier-based hydrogen A kinetic model of the hydrogen release unit and system performance

Sentencas: A system layout is described and investigated according to its transient operating behavior and its efficiency.

Sentencas: We demonstrate that the maximum efficiency of LOHC-bound hydrogen-to-electricity is 45% at full load, avoiding any critical conditions for the system components.
